{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3151", "repo": "rails", "body": "Is this really worth it? \r\nObviously we don't want logic in our views, but compare these two:\r\n\r\n`\"<b>#{count}</b> #{pluralize(count, \"dog\", :include_count => false)}\"`\r\n\r\nvs the basic condtion\r\n\r\n`\"<b>#{count}</b> #{count == 1 ? \"dog\" : \"dog\".pluralize}\"`\r\n\r\nThe second version is shorter and expresses the functionality clearly.\r\n\r\nMaybe a better solution would be to just tweak the pluralize String method to take an optional parameter of count.\r\n\r\n`<b>#{count}</b> #{\"dog\".pluralize(count)}`", "_id": {"$oid": "52383a17bd3543c151010168"}, "issue_id": 3151, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2219004", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3151#issuecomment-2219004", "updated_at": "2011-09-28T02:38:47Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/et", "login": "et", "gravatar_id": "3787c05a986fc71117e4a83bc47c9637", "html_url": "https://github.com/et", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3787c05a986fc71117e4a83bc47c9637?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8257fe03047e82b57406ed493c6e8913.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 58678, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-09-28T02:38:47Z", "id": 2219004, "owner": "rails"}
